'''[[abbey]]-[[lubber]]'''
#{{archaic}}: term of contempt for an able-bodied idler who grew sleek and fat from the charity of religious houses; sometimes applied to monks
#*'''1681:''' This is no huge overgrown '''abbey-lubber'''. - [[w:John Dryden|John Dryden]], ''The Spanish Fryar'', III-iii